    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      r1 closed 2026-06-01 with `Failed: 0` across both BFF test suites, anti-drift codified, CI gate restored. r2 inherits a clean test-runtime state but a 20-entry real-bug ledger as production-fix backlog. Without a measured baseline, "we fixed 20 real-bug entries" is unverifiable. This task is the first link in the Phase 0 chain (000 → 001 → 002) and the measurement anchor every subsequent phase cites in its delta artifact (NFR-06).
    </background>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/r1-closeout-2026-06-01.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read r1's exit-ledger (`projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/exit-ledger.md`) and post-phase23-authoritative baseline; extract the r1-final test counts for both `Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests` and `Spe.Integration.Tests`.</step>
    <step order="2">Read r1's `real-bug-ledger.md`; tabulate the 20 entries by severity (5 HIGH / 7 MED / 8 LOW) and capture each entry's current Status field as the r2-baseline state.</step>
    <step order="3">Run `gh api repos/spaarke-dev/spaarke/branches/master/protection` to capture current branch-protection state (`enforce_admins`, required status checks); confirm `enforce_admins: true` is restored post-r1 PR #314.</step>
    <step order="4">Read `.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml`; capture the gate state (Coverlet lines 85-102 wired; duplicate-YAML-key fix in place per r1 task 002).</step>
    <step order="5">Verify the 4 anti-drift artifacts exist + reference each other: `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F; `.github/pull_request_template.md`; `docs/procedures/testing-and-code-quality.md`; root `CLAUDE.md` §10 bullet 6.</step>
    <step order="6">Author `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/r1-closeout-2026-06-01.md` with sections: r1 final test counts; 20-entry ledger inventory + severity counts; branch-protection state; CI workflow state; anti-drift mechanisms in place; r2 forward-target deltas (per-phase exit gate).</step>
    <step order="7">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` (create if absent) — mark 000 as ✅.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion note + cite the baseline file path.</step>
    <step order="9">Commit message: "docs(projects/r2): capture r1 close-out baseline (NFR-06)" — references NFR-06.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">r1 exit-ledger, real-bug-ledger, sdap-ci.yml, bff-extensions.md</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">`gh api` for branch-protection state; `git status` for boundary verification</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create the baseline artifact</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/r1-closeout-2026-06-01.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`baseline/r1-closeout-2026-06-01.md` exists and includes all 6 sections: test counts, ledger inventory, branch-protection state, CI state, anti-drift artifacts, r2 forward-target deltas</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">20-entry ledger inventory enumerates each entry with: ID, severity, current Status field, fix-by date</criterion>
